UML:TaggedValue.value: Overview: an AnimationWindow is an area on the screen in which a bouncing ball animation occurs. AnimationWindows have two modes: on and off. During the on mode the ball moves, during the off mode the ball doesn't move.
@effects initializes this to be in the off mode.
Repaints the Graphics area g. Swing will then send the newly painted g to the screen.

Turns the animation on/off. mode=true if running mode, mode=false if building mode.
Boolean indicating if animation is on/off
x,y is the [CENTER] of the square, r is the radius (that is, from the center to the left border).
